caption:
WE HAD SO MUCH FUN PACKING OUT THIS BEER. 

For Pride this year, we thought it would be a great idea to have the queer folks and allies on staff design a beer for pride and participate in brewing it together.

The team decided that they wanted to do a Berliner Weisse with peaches and blackberries.

This label is inspired by the first pride, which was was a RIOT. The anti-gay discrimination and violence that was happening in 1969 is still happening to queer and trans communities today. Make your voice heard. Get out and vote for folks who support queer communities, and reach out to your policymakers to pass non-discrimination laws at the local, state, and federal level.

In mid June we plan to have a Pride event where folks will have the opportunity to write letters to NC policy makers and learn about what‚Äôs going on around LGBTQ+ rights in our state (especially with all the anti-trans bills). Stay tuned for that. 

Part of the sales from this beer supports the @lgbtqdurham 

Thanks to our queer and trans elders who paved the way, and inspire us to continue to do the work.

This beer drops at @fullsteamdrm today, and @fullsteamrtp and the triangle area very soon!!

caption:
Congratulations to Leadership Triangle's Emerging Leaders 2024! Yesterday, these fantastic North Carolina Central University and Shaw University students graduated from the program and were officially inducted into the Goodmon Fellowship.

The Emerging Leaders Program, powered by Capitol Broadcasting Company and Leadership Triangle, is designed to recognize, support, and develop the immense emerging talent at Triangle-based HBCUs.

Through the program, each student interned with Capitol Broadcasting Company, participated in leadership development workshops with Leadership Triangle, and received 1:1 coaching from Triangle-based leaders and mentors. In total, each student completed 400 hours with the Emerging Leaders Program. We could not be more proud of this amazing group of young leaders!!

‚ÄúThank you Leadership Triangle for helping me see what was already within me, and helping me become the leader I aspire to be.‚Äù - Margot Schein, 2024 Transforming Leaders Goodmon Fellow

It‚Äôs 2025. What‚Äôs out?
- Equating positional authority with leadership.
- Rigid leadership frameworks that no one actually uses.
- Sitting in leadership workshops and learning passively from ‚Äúexperts‚Äù.

In?
- Working to clarify your own values, understand your bias, and hone your style.
- Taking charge of the impact you have on others; reducing your blindspots.
- Shaping your own learning experience and learning from peers. 

If you started this year with a goal of getting a promotion, changing jobs, or just figuring a little bit more out about yourself, Transforming Leaders is the program for you.

We have a few spots remaining in our Spring cohort. Apply today to secure yours.

‚ÄúI highly recommend Leadership Triangle to anyone new - or old - to the community who really cares about the Triangle and wants to see it thrive.‚Äù - Courtney Bagans, Regional 2024 Goodmon Fellow 

Connection to inspiring leaders, information about key issues that will shape our future, and a ton of fun. If that sounds good to you, sign up for our newsletter and keep yourself in the loop around all of Leadership Triangle‚Äôs programs and events! #GoodmonFellows

The Secret Agents Ball is a North Carolina Kiki Ballroom scene affiliated event and the theme is inspired by our favorite assassins, ninjas or secret agent film and pop-culture figures. 

Years ago, The Triangle housed an intimate ballroom community, which over the years, became concentrated in larger metropolitan areas like Charlotte. This event will serve as a revival for the Ballroom scene in the Durham and greater Triangle community and eventually serve as an annual event. 

The Secret Agents Ball will be hosted by Vanity Bodega and Kinky Bodega of the North Carolina Chapter of The Elite Kiki House of Bodega and The LGBTQ Center of Durham at @rickhousedurham Downtown Durham on Thursday May 18, 2023 with Doors opening at 5pm and the first category starting at 6pm. 

Participating in or walking a category at this ‚ÄúOf The Year‚Äù approved function will qualify you for competitive nominations throughout the North Carolina Kiki Ballroom connection.
